{{der-top|Compounds with irregular readings of {{lang|ja|刀}}}}
* {{ja-r|薙刀|なぎなた}}: a traditional Japanese [[halberd]]
* {{ja-r|太刀|たち}}: a traditional Japanese [[longsword]]
* {{ja-r|馬刀貝|まてがい}}: a [[razor clam]]
{{der-bottom}}

{{ja-noun|かたな}}

# {{lb|ja|sort=かたな|weapons}} a single-[[edge]]d [[sword]], such as a [[katana]]
#* {{quote-book|||Vol.5
|||date=Sep 23 1999
|publisher={{w|Konami}}
|lang=ja
|chapter={{lj|[鎧](よろい)[武](む)[者](しゃ)ゾンビ}}
|trans-chapter=Armored Musha Zombie}}
#*: {{ja-usex|怨%念により蘇った武%者。闇%雲にふりまわす'''カタナ'''に注%意。|おん%ねん に より よみがえった む%しゃ。やみ%くも に ふりまわす '''カタナ''' に ちゅう%い。|A musha reanimated by deep hatred. Watch out when he brandishes his katana.}}
# a small single-edged [[blade]]

{{der-top}}
* {{ja-r|刀%市|かたな% いち}}: a [[sword]] [[market]]
* {{ja-r|刀%引|かたな%びき}}: [[giving]] a [[sword]] worn on one's hip to another as a [[gift]] at a [[banquet]] or other social [[gathering]]
{{der-mid}}
* {{ja-r|小%刀|こ%がたな}}: a small [[knife]], a [[penknife]], a [[pocketknife]], a [[jackknife]]
* {{ja-r|腰%刀|こし%がたな}}: a hip-sword, smaller than a katana and with no {{m|ja|鍔|tr=tsuba||sword guard}}
{{der-bottom}}

{{der-top|Idioms}}
* {{ja-r|刀 折れ 矢 尽きる|かたな おれ や つきる}}: “swords bent, out of arrows” → completely [[rout]]ed, a complete [[loss]] in [[battle]]
* {{ja-r|刀 に 懸けて|かたな に かけて}}: “[depending, swearing] on one's sword” → a metaphor for [[firm]] [[resolve]] to see something through
* {{ja-r|刀 の 錆び|かたな の さび}}: “sword [[rust]]” → a metaphor for killing someone or being killed, from the way that [[blood]] can cause the [[steel]] of a sword to rust; a [[derogatory]] term for someone who isn't even worth [[soil]]ing a sword
{{der-bottom}}

